						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone standing near the temple of Basavaṇṇa in S. No. 240.</hi></p>						

						<p>Vikramāditya VI (No date).</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription referring itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanamalladēva</hi> records that a hero died in a fight. He bore a number of epithets. The characters belong to about 11-12th century A.D.</p>						

